<p>A paragraph is a unit of writing that expresses a single main idea, typically consisting of a topic sentence, supporting sentences, and a concluding sentence.
Definition and Purpose
A paragraph is a group of sentences that form a coherent unit, focusing on one main idea or theme, often called the controlling idea, which guides the content of the paragraph (Lunsford and Connors). Paragraphs are the building blocks of essays, research papers, and other written works, helping readers follow the organization and logic of the text. They can vary in length, sometimes being a single sentence in journalistic or creative writing, but the key is unity and coherence of ideas. 
